The meaning is, it was quite natural and intelligible that elo· quence should come to be regarded as indispensable for the ‘cursus honorum ’: even in less official situations the need for it was often felt. Then follows a regular sequence of (1) public assemblies (ad populum), (2) meetings of senate (iu senatu), and (3) courts of law, either (a) as defendant (invidiam . . . crimen), or (b) as a witness (testimonia quoque).
